      <h1>Winners</h1> 
      <p>Congratulations to this year's winners!<p>
      <p>2015</p>
      <p><strong>Winner:</strong> Gregory Clark</p>
      <p><strong>Honorable Mention:</strong> Maria Markovich and Daniel Rorabaugh</p>

      <h2>Spirit of the Award </h2>
      <p> The Peer Excellence Award is presented to a graduate student on behalf of their fellow
	  graduate students. The award recognizes the laudable contributions students make to their 
	  peers and the scholarly environment.   
      </p>
  
      <h3>Current Peer Excellence Award Committee</h3> 
      <p> Sameed Ahmed - Wilson Harvey - Erik Palmer - Maya Stephenson -  Robert Wilcox 
      </p> 


      <h2>History </h2> 
      <p> The Peer Excellence Award was founded in 2015 by some graduate students in 
          LC122. 
      </p>

      <h2>FAQ:</h2>
      <p><strong>Why is it called the Peer Excellence Award?</strong><br>
         It is an Award chosen by our Peers in recognition of Excellence. Also, no one 
	 has paid $100 to have the award named after themselves. <br><br>
	 <strong>When will the award be presented?</strong><br>
	 Monday, April 27th at 3:45pm in the Wyman Williams room during the Department 
	 Awards ceremony.
	 <br><br>
	 <strong>Do I have to be present to win?</strong><br>
	 Yes. If you are not present your name will be scratched out and replaced with the
	 name of the runner-up. <br><br>
	 <strong>How do I choose who to vote for?</strong><br>
	 Vote for the graduate student that is the most excellent. You get to define excellence.
	 For help, Webster's Dictionary defines excellence as "the quality of being excellent."
	 <br><br>
      </p>

      <h2>Support the Peer Excellence Award</h2> 

